ides: Observations and model results (2011) J. Geophys. Res., , doi:10.1029/ 2010JC006387 in press; Pawlowicz, R., Beardsley, B., Lentz, S., Classical tidal harmonic analysis including error estimates in MATLAB using TDE (2002) Computers and Geosciences, 28 (8), pp. 929-937. , DOI 10.1016/S0098-3004(02)00013-4, PII S0098300402000134; Polyakov, I.V., Alexee, V.A., Bhatt, U.S., Polyakova, E.I., Zhang, X., North Atlantic warming: Patterns of long-term trend and multi-decadal variability (2009) Clim. Dyn., 34, pp. 439-457; Ray, R.D., Secular changes of the M<inf>2</inf> tide in the Gulf of Maine (2006) Continental Shelf Research, 26 (3), pp. 422-427. , DOI 10.1016/j.csr.2005.12.005, PII S0278434306000033; Ray, R.D., Secular changes in the solar semidiurnal tide of the western North Atlantic Ocean (2009) Geophys. Res. Lett., 36, pp. L19601. , doi:10.1029/2009GL040217; St-Laurent, P., Saucier, F.J., Dumais, J.-F., On the modification of tides in a seasonally ice-covered sea (2008) J. Geophys. Res., 113, pp. C11014. , doi:10.1029/2007JC004614; Woodworth, P.L., A survey of recent changes in the main components of the ocean tide (2010) Cont. Shelf Res., 30, pp. 1680-1691; Woodworth, P.L., Shaw, S.M., Blackman, D.L., Secular trends in mean tidal range around the British Isles and along the adjacent European coastline (1991) Geophys. J. Int., 104, pp. 593-609","Müller, M.; School of Earth and Ocean Sciences, University of Victoria, PO Box 1700, Victoria, BC V8W 2Y2, Canada; email: mmueller@uvic.ca",,,"Blackwell Publishing Ltd",,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-79958107649
